Detailed Description

Superclass to OverviewMatch and VanillaMatch.

FIXME: Do something about the names and when to delete them. FIXME: Add flags to load and save so that the regions are saved in a more compact fashion.

uint8 SearchMatch::getRestrictions (   )  const [inline]
 

Get the search restrictions that were used to get this match.

Bit 1Is set if we were doing close matching instead of exact matching.
Bit 2Is set if we were searching in BUAs instead of city parts.
Bit 3Is set if we were searching in Municipals instead of BUAs.
Bit 4Is set if we were searching anywhere in the string instead of in the beginning of the string.
Bit 5Is set if we were searching in the whole map without location masking.
Bit 6Is set if we were ignoring any category masking.
Bit 7Is set if we were trying phonetic search.
Bit 8Is set if we were trying to change the search string.

Returns:
the restrictions from the search. It contains 8 bits.
